The Police Command in Kano has rescued a 10-year-old girl confined to a room for 10 years by her biological parents. The Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Abdullahi Haruna, disclosed this in a statement on Tuesday. The spokesman said 297 suspects were also apprehended in continuation of efforts to rid the state of crimes. The arrests were made between April 10 and May 23 â€“ before, during and after the festive Eid-el-Fitr celebration. Different criminal hideouts and black spots were raided during the period. The suspects include 187 suspected thugs, one suspected ATM fraudster and one suspected human trafficker. Others are 80 suspected fraudsters, armed robbers, five suspected drug dealers, seven suspected livestock and phone thieves. Also in custody are seven suspected kidnappers and a gun dealer, seven car thieves, cattle rustlers and two others caught with fake American dollars. Screwdriver, masking tape, plastic ruler and pistol with the empty shell of .9mm ammunition were recovered. Other were vehicles, tricycles, motorcycles, mobile phones, illicit drugs such as cocaine, rubber solutions and suck and die. They would be charged to court upon completion of investigations, he said. Ogun: Man defiles his three teenage daughters, another 10-year-old girl 